<sect>The KDE Control Center
<p>

The KDE Control Center provides a convenient way to access all the
configuration modules. In principle, the configuration modules are
independent programs. They can be executed using the Settings menu,
the command line, or the Control Center.
<p>
The Control Center shows all the  modules in a list, so it is easier 
to find the right configuration module.

<sect> The Configuration Modules
<p>

This is a list of the <it>standard</it> configuration modules provided by the
KDE base package. Please note that there may be many more modules on your system
if you install additional software. You can access the help for any module
by first selecting the module in the control center and the pressing the
help button.
